description:
At our Compost Hubs, food scraps collected from the community are transformed into nutrient-rich compost, and we need your help to make it happen! As a Compost Hub Support Volunteer, you’ll gain hands-on experience working alongside our knowledgeable Compost Managers. Get ready to leave feeling accomplished, a little sweaty, and brimming with new compost knowledge. 

#### ABOUT ACTIVITY:
Roll up your sleeves and dive into a variety of engaging activities—whether it’s managing a three-bin system, tending to a compost pile, sifting finished compost, or exploring a mix of everything. There’s something for everyone, from beginners to seasoned pros! Plus, our Compost Hubs are situated in LA County’s most cherished green spaces: community gardens, urban farms, and beautiful parks. Join passionate community composters, learn to turn food scraps into rich compost, and connect with the local food system. 

#### MORE INFO: 
* You will be working outdoors! Shade levels vary by site.
* Activities level can be adjusted to your comfort and abilities—just communicate with your Compost Manager.
* No prior composting experience is needed; everyone is welcome!
* This site has public bathrooms
* If you sign up, we ask that you show up! We rely on volunteers, like you, to achieve our mission.  
* We’ll follow up with details via email, so be sure to provide your best contact email when signing up.

#### AGE REQUIREMENT:
This volunteer activity is best suited for volunteers aged 16 and up. Minors under the age of 16 should come accompanied by a parent or guardian unless other arrangements are made. Contact ashleigh@lacompost.org for more information.

#### IMPORTANT: VOLUNTEER WAIVER
Please make sure you have signed the volunteer waiver. 
Access the e-wavier at https://www.lacompost.org/waiver

title: ALABAMA: Rapid Response for Our Freedoms
description:
Are you alarmed by the far-right's **relentless push to dismantle our democracy** and undermine our future? The *time to act is now*—your voice and involvement are vital in this critical moment.

Together, we have the power to **resist this dangerous agenda** that seeks to replace our democracy with authoritarian rule. By organizing, mobilizing, and holding leaders accountable, we can **protect the rights, freedoms, and values that define America.**

Join us for **"Rapid Response for Our Freedoms,"** a crucial event where we **stand as one to defend democracy**, *uphold the rule of law,* and safeguard the **rights and freedoms we all hold dear.** 

*This is our moment to rise up* for an America that includes everyone when we say *"liberty and justice for all," * not just the wealthy and powerful.

### Goals of the Event:

-To **mobilize and activate** a network of people ready to take **immediate, strategic action** to defend our *rights, freedoms, the rule of law, and democracy.*

-To **educate and inform** participants about current *authoritarian threats, legal overreach, and* **coordinated attacks on our freedoms.**

-To share **concrete tools, tactics, and next steps** that individuals and groups can take in their communities to *push back.*

-To build a **connected movement** rooted in *collective power, solidarity, and a shared vision of justice and equality for all*—not just the wealthy, powerful, or those with privilege.

### What You'll Take Away: 

-A **clear understanding** of the threats we face—and the *power we have to overcome them.*

-**Action steps** you can take *immediately* to protect our rights, freedoms, the rule of law, and democracy.

-**Resources** for organizing *locally and nationally* with other committed members of People Power United.

-To share **concrete tools, tactics, and next steps** that individuals and groups can take in their communities to *push back.*

-To build a **connected movement** rooted in *collective power, solidarity, and a shared vision of justice and equality for all*—not just the wealthy, powerful, or those with privilege.

### What You'll Take Away: 

-A **clear understanding** of the threats we face—and the *power we have to overcome them.*

-**Action steps** you can take *immediately* to protect our rights, freedoms, the rule of law, and democracy.

-**Resources** for organizing *locally and nationally* with other committed members of People Power United.

-A **renewed sense of purpose, community, and hope**—knowing *you're not alone* in this fight.

The strength of **people power is unstoppable**—together, *we can and will make a difference.*

At **People Power United**, we believe in **progress** and the strength of **collective action**. Together, we can push back against extremism and **build a brighter future.** Join us in the fight for **Freedom over Fascism** and help *amplify the power of people* to shape our democracy!

description: Join us to learn about our ongoing work for climate justice in Pittsburgh!! The general body meeting is a space for our teams to share progress and needs for our current campaign. If you want to get involved (or re-involved) with our hub, the general body meeting is a great place to understand how our hubs works and what your role could be in it.

description:

Sharing Field Team 6 ready-made posts

Tips & Tricks for getting the most out of Bluesky

title: Forests for Indy: Make Plans to Attend City Council Meetings
description:
We are expecting good news for urban forests at the upcoming City-County Council meeting! Please join us to show your support.

Having a strong presence at every council meeting shows support for our urban forests to the Councilors and the Mayor's Office.

A group will march from the IFA building (615 N Alabama St) at 6:30. Otherwise, please meet us at the City-County Council building.

description: Join the GLDC for Topical Presentations, Short Business Meeting and Liberal Discussion.  Third Monday of the month (except July, August and December)

description: Join us for our monthly meeting at 2:00pm on the 2nd Sunday of each month. Our current focus is the upcoming session of the Texas Legislature, where we will support and defend public education, gun control, and healthcare for all, among other issues. In Texas those are uphill battles and we need you now more than ever before!

title: Greening Day at Sunset Blvd Gardens (37th Ave and Santiago)
description:
We need your help keeping our native gardens beautiful and free of weeds. Our goal is to build habitat and promote biodiversity with local native plants, which will support local pollinators and wildlife in a corridor that connects Lake Merced and Golden Gate Park. 

Volunteers will meet at 37th and Santiago.

Please sign up so we can prepare enough tools for everyone. 

### What to Bring/Wear
- Bring a reusable water bottle 
- Wear closed toe shoes
- Dress in layers 

### Community Partners
California Native Plant Society Yerba Buena Chapter, SF Public Works

description: Join the Pinal County Democratic Chair virtually in an informal discussion with other Democrats and friends. This is an opportunity to ask questions, share ideas, and learn about what is happening in your Democratic Party.

description:
Meet fellow Democrats and review and implement the action plan to put Democrats in office at the local, state and national level. Meet local candidates for office and work towards winning elections. We focus on boots-on-the ground activities such as meeting voters and encouraging them to cast their ballots, collecting mail ballot requests and building our neighborhood volunteer teams.

Social and Ordering off the menu @6

title: 2025 GCDP East Oxford + Credle Precinct Cluster Meetings
description:
Join us for the GCDP East Oxford + Credle Precinct Monthly Meeting this March! We'll gather to discuss our upcoming initiatives for 2025 and plan our strategy as we head toward municipal elections in November! 

This is a great opportunity to connect with fellow Democrats, stay informed, and actively contribute to the political landscape in our community. 

Join us at the GCDP HQ on Tuesday, March 18th at 6:30 PM.

Whether you're a long-time party member or a newcomer interested in getting involved, your voice matters, and we welcome your participation. Let's work together to make a positive impact in East Oxford + Credle and beyond!

title: 2025 Young Democrats of Granville County Monthly Meeting
description:
Join us for an engaging evening of Democratic dialogue and community involvement at the Young Democrats of Granville County monthly meeting. Whether you're a long-time party supporter or just a supporter of Democratic values, this event is your opportunity to get informed, ask questions, and connect with fellow Democrats.

We will also be discussing our vision and plans for 2025 at this meeting. Join us, and bring a friend!

P.S. While acting members of the Young Democrats must be between the ages of 16-36, all are welcome to join us!

title: Custer County Monthly Breakfast
description:
***No May 3rd Breakfast due to McGovern Day Rally on the same day***

The Custer County Democratic Party holds a monthly breakfast gathering on the first Saturday of each month. It starts at 9:15am MT at Laughing Water Restaurant at Crazy Horse Memorial. It's a time and place for like minded people to enjoy a meal and share meaningful conversations. Please RSVP by emailing ccsddp21info@gmail.com. This is to get an accurate head count for the restaurant.

title: County Convention & Monthly Meetings - Granville County Democratic Party
description:
This April, join us for the 2025 Granville County Democratic Party County Convention! This is your opportunity to build grassroots power in your community, elect precinct leadership, and strengthen our Democratic movement ahead of critical upcoming elections.

At this meeting, we will:

✅ Elect our chairs, vice chairs, and secretary

✅ Vote on any resolutions

✅ Elect delegates to represent our community at Congressional District Conventions

✅ Elect delegates to the NCDP State Executive Committee

✅ Learn about upcoming training and voter outreach opportunities

Your participation is essential! North Carolina elections are decided by just a handful of votes per precinct, and your engagement makes the difference. Come meet your neighbors, get involved, and help build a stronger, more organized Democratic Party.

💙 Let’s get organized and WIN in 2025!

RSVP now to be part of the movement!

title: RuCo Action Monthly Meetings 2025
description:
Join us for our monthly meetings where we plan ways to engage with our community to fight for reproductive justice! We have a lot of work to do in 2025 and we want you to join us in the fight! Come out and learn how you can help. 

RuCo Action is a Planned Parenthood Action Council that works to build power in our local community by advocating for reproductive justice, sexual healthcare access, and bodily autonomy.
